1
00:00:43,043 --> 00:00:46,464
CHAPTER 1:
I AM A WEB NOVEL WRITER

2
00:00:52,636 --> 00:00:55,765
Yeon-hui had been friends with Ho
since childhood.

3
00:00:55,848 --> 00:00:56,682
HO
BITTER-SWEET HEART

4
00:00:56,766 --> 00:00:58,976
He's a man of few words and can be blunt,

5
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:01,729
but the way he takes care of her
makes her heart swoon.

6
00:01:02,605 --> 00:01:03,939
She met Jin in college.

7
00:01:04,565 --> 00:01:05,691
JIN
RAY OF SUNSHINE

8
00:01:05,775 --> 00:01:08,277
He's so sweet you'd think he's an angel.

9
00:01:09,236 --> 00:01:10,821
Fans are split between

10
00:01:11,655 --> 00:01:14,116
shipping YeonHo

11
00:01:14,909 --> 00:01:17,411
and YeonJin

12
00:01:17,495 --> 00:01:18,621
as the ultimate couple.

13
00:01:19,538 --> 00:01:20,664
But personally…

14
00:01:27,463 --> 00:01:29,298
I told you never to show your face again.

15
00:01:29,840 --> 00:01:32,718
You drive me so crazy I can't stand it.

16
00:01:33,344 --> 00:01:34,178
Why?

17
00:01:34,970 --> 00:01:36,013
Why on earth?

18
00:01:39,517 --> 00:01:41,685
Why couldn't we have met sooner?

19
00:01:43,312 --> 00:01:44,772
…I'm all in on HoJin.

20
00:01:46,816 --> 00:01:49,485
-Idiot.
-The desperation in their eyes

21
00:01:49,568 --> 00:01:51,237
from having to hide their true feelings.

22
00:02:01,539 --> 00:02:02,373
Sorry.

23
00:02:04,625 --> 00:02:05,459
Hello, dad.

24
00:02:06,418 --> 00:02:07,253
What did you say?

25
00:02:07,336 --> 00:02:09,380
I've decided to remarry Geum-yeong.

26
00:02:09,463 --> 00:02:11,423
From now on, you and Ho are brothers.

27
00:02:13,467 --> 00:02:15,302
I hope you'll get along
as well as you do now.

28
00:02:20,182 --> 00:02:21,392
Hang on a moment.

29
00:02:23,102 --> 00:02:25,229
I can't take this anymore.

30
00:02:25,312 --> 00:02:26,689
Are you out of your mind?

31
00:02:29,817 --> 00:02:30,943
Hey! I'm talking to you!

32
00:02:32,820 --> 00:02:33,654
Sorry?

33
00:02:33,737 --> 00:02:35,865
Didn't you say this is the last episode?

34
00:02:38,158 --> 00:02:40,411
-Right.
-Yet you're pulling this kind of crap?

35
00:02:40,494 --> 00:02:43,455
I've put up with everything so far,
but the story is dragging so much.

36
00:02:43,539 --> 00:02:47,334
How can they only find out
they like each other in the last episode?

37
00:02:47,418 --> 00:02:49,962
And then out of the blue
they become brothers?

38
00:02:50,546 --> 00:02:51,422
What a crock!

39
00:02:51,505 --> 00:02:55,092
Well, we might get a season two.

40
00:02:56,343 --> 00:02:57,177
Are you insane?

41
00:02:57,261 --> 00:03:00,389
You think you'll get a season two
after this nonsense?

42
00:03:00,472 --> 00:03:03,559
Nobody even wants to read your novel!

43
00:03:04,810 --> 00:03:06,145
That's harsh.

44
00:03:06,896 --> 00:03:07,813
Is that her?

45
00:03:08,397 --> 00:03:11,317
The hack author whose characters,
plot, structure and writing

46
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:14,153
are all a complete mess?

47
00:03:28,292 --> 00:03:29,293
Where is she?

48
00:03:30,085 --> 00:03:31,545
-Over there.
-Arrest her.

49
00:03:38,052 --> 00:03:40,137
Hands up! Step away from the keyboard!

50
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:41,263
Don't touch that!

51
00:03:41,347 --> 00:03:42,806
-What…
-Hands in the air!

52
00:03:43,307 --> 00:03:45,309
What did I do?

53
00:03:45,392 --> 00:03:48,062
You know as well as anyone
how much your novel sucks.

54
00:03:49,229 --> 00:03:51,440
Writing a novel that sucks

55
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:54,818
isn't a crime!

56
00:03:54,902 --> 00:03:56,111
Oh, yes it is!

57
00:03:57,363 --> 00:03:59,031
Article 1, Clause 1 of the Web Novel Act.

58
00:03:59,114 --> 00:04:01,450
Boring authors shall be punished.

59
00:04:01,533 --> 00:04:02,910
Accordingly, Yeo Eui-ju,

60
00:04:03,661 --> 00:04:04,828
I'm arresting you.

61
00:04:04,912 --> 00:04:05,996
No. You can't.

62
00:04:07,081 --> 00:04:08,499
No.

63
00:04:08,582 --> 00:04:11,502
No!

64
00:04:21,971 --> 00:04:23,681
I really thought I'd been arrested.

65
00:04:28,394 --> 00:04:31,021
PAZER WEB NOVEL PORTAL

66
00:04:38,070 --> 00:04:39,321
I'm…

67
00:04:39,405 --> 00:04:40,948
PAZER WEB NOVEL PORTAL

68
00:04:41,532 --> 00:04:42,449
…a writer.

69
00:04:45,119 --> 00:04:46,996
My genre is…

70
00:04:47,913 --> 00:04:49,999
BL.

71
00:04:50,082 --> 00:04:51,375
BL: ABBREVIATION OF BOYS' LOVE

72
00:04:51,458 --> 00:04:53,043
PRIZE
WRITING CONTEST

73
00:04:54,545 --> 00:04:55,838
My pen name is

74
00:04:57,047 --> 00:04:57,965
Imuk.

75
00:04:59,717 --> 00:05:01,093
My novel…

76
00:05:01,176 --> 00:05:02,845
THEY CAME TOGETHER

77
00:05:02,928 --> 00:05:04,388
…has only been read by me.

78
00:05:05,973 --> 00:05:08,809
The one with two views
was just a random click.

79
00:05:10,185 --> 00:05:13,313
They could've at least
left a snarky comment.

80
00:05:14,398 --> 00:05:16,608
ZERO REVIEWS

81
00:05:23,824 --> 00:05:24,783
Yeo Eui-do.

82
00:05:26,076 --> 00:05:28,495
The only person
who knows I write BL web novels.

83
00:05:29,621 --> 00:05:30,622
Coke.

84
00:05:30,706 --> 00:05:32,124
YEO EUI-DO
COKE ADDICT BROTHER

85
00:05:32,916 --> 00:05:35,169
He's using it to blackmail me.

86
00:05:38,964 --> 00:05:41,759
EPISODE 1

87
00:05:46,805 --> 00:05:48,891
What am I going to write next?

88
00:05:50,517 --> 00:05:52,728
I can't afford another bomb.

89
00:06:15,125 --> 00:06:17,669
Your leg must be sore. It's really tight.

90
00:06:17,753 --> 00:06:18,962
Did you shower?

91
00:06:19,046 --> 00:06:20,672
You smell great.

92
00:06:20,756 --> 00:06:22,091
Is that what I bought for you?

93
00:06:25,385 --> 00:06:28,263
You're so tense. We'd better keep at it.

94
00:06:32,267 --> 00:06:33,769
Get up.

95
00:06:33,852 --> 00:06:35,020
Let's work on your top.

96
00:06:35,104 --> 00:06:36,355
Not here!

97
00:06:36,438 --> 00:06:37,981
Then let's go inside.

98
00:06:39,441 --> 00:06:42,069
It's too early for that!

99
00:06:44,988 --> 00:06:46,532
Did you sleep well last night?

100
00:06:47,407 --> 00:06:49,368
I couldn't sleep at all because of you.

101
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:51,537
Because you weren't there.

102
00:06:54,623 --> 00:06:56,041
Tonight,

103
00:06:56,125 --> 00:06:57,793
-I don't want to be alone.
-I don't want to be alone.

104
00:07:11,306 --> 00:07:12,432
What's up with her?

105
00:07:12,516 --> 00:07:13,684
Is she here for me?

106
00:07:14,309 --> 00:07:16,436
-Wasn't that a dude?
-It was a girl.

107
00:07:17,271 --> 00:07:19,273
-Are your eyes okay?
-They're fine.

108
00:07:19,356 --> 00:07:20,607
What's up with Dong-ju?

109
00:07:20,691 --> 00:07:21,525
He got a cramp.

110
00:07:21,608 --> 00:07:22,734
Why did Gi-jeon carry him?

111
00:07:22,818 --> 00:07:23,861
For the exercise.

112
00:07:26,155 --> 00:07:28,657
CHAPTER 2:
DO YOU KNOW WHY STUDENTS WEAR UNIFORMS?

113
00:07:28,740 --> 00:07:30,826
EUI-JU'S HOUSE
SHIN, YOON-JU, EUI-JU, EUI-DO, SUNI

114
00:07:35,038 --> 00:07:36,623
Hey, mom,

115
00:07:36,707 --> 00:07:40,002
have the twins who used to live
at the white house move away?

116
00:07:41,086 --> 00:07:42,004
Have they?

117
00:07:43,380 --> 00:07:46,425
It looks like a bunch of guys
have moved in.

118
00:07:46,508 --> 00:07:47,384
Really?

119
00:07:48,010 --> 00:07:50,888
I heard the twins' dad got promoted.
Maybe he transferred to HQ.

120
00:07:50,971 --> 00:07:52,431
Why didn't they say goodbye?

121
00:07:54,141 --> 00:07:55,100
What about us?

122
00:07:55,934 --> 00:07:57,519
When are we moving?

123
00:07:59,188 --> 00:08:00,272
Don't you like it here?

124
00:08:01,148 --> 00:08:02,608
I turned down a promotion.

125
00:08:07,779 --> 00:08:09,907
Eat up.

126
00:08:15,746 --> 00:08:16,830
Pervert!

127
00:08:21,251 --> 00:08:22,669
I'm done.

128
00:08:25,464 --> 00:08:26,715
Have some more.

129
00:08:26,798 --> 00:08:29,009
If I have more, I'll be late.

130
00:08:31,011 --> 00:08:32,554
See you later.

131
00:08:33,972 --> 00:08:36,016
-Have a good day!
-Watch out for cars!

132
00:08:40,979 --> 00:08:42,022
I said I'd go by myself.

133
00:08:42,105 --> 00:08:45,025
Why are you being so stubborn?
Let's go together.

134
00:08:45,108 --> 00:08:47,361
I hate the smell
of the air freshener in that car.

135
00:08:48,487 --> 00:08:49,780
Hang on.

136
00:08:54,368 --> 00:08:55,285
I'll go with you.

137
00:08:56,036 --> 00:08:58,038
Forget it. Mind your own business.

138
00:08:58,121 --> 00:08:59,414
What's this?

139
00:08:59,498 --> 00:09:01,250
Isn't that those guys from yesterday?

140
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:02,501
Hey, Ga Woo-su!

141
00:09:06,004 --> 00:09:07,339
I can't.

142
00:09:09,633 --> 00:09:11,927
-You know I can't.
-Give it a rest!

143
00:09:12,010 --> 00:09:13,762
Unbelievable!

144
00:09:14,513 --> 00:09:15,389
You're annoying me.

145
00:09:16,098 --> 00:09:16,974
A lovers' spat?

146
00:09:17,557 --> 00:09:19,184
Just listen to me. Please.

147
00:09:21,019 --> 00:09:22,604
Until when?

148
00:09:23,313 --> 00:09:25,565
Let's just take the car and make it easy.

149
00:09:25,649 --> 00:09:27,818
How long do I have to do what you want?

150
00:09:27,901 --> 00:09:28,902
I said I'd go by myself.

151
00:09:28,986 --> 00:09:31,154
What an asshole!

152
00:09:32,197 --> 00:09:34,825
The guys are almost ready.
Just give them a minute.

153
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:37,911
What a nice guy.

154
00:09:37,995 --> 00:09:39,538
He'll be kicking himself later.

155
00:09:44,042 --> 00:09:45,419
Don't be such a drama queen.

156
00:09:46,044 --> 00:09:48,213
-Woo-su!
-I hope it's not stuck to my forehead.

157
00:09:56,430 --> 00:09:57,306
Wait here.

158
00:10:12,654 --> 00:10:14,031
What a hottie!

159
00:10:15,449 --> 00:10:16,283
You were filming.

160
00:10:18,618 --> 00:10:21,204
-Sorry?
-I saw you. Delete it.

161
00:10:22,247 --> 00:10:23,081
I wasn't.

162
00:10:23,165 --> 00:10:25,625
I was just trying to see
if I had a bug on my face.

163
00:10:29,963 --> 00:10:32,924
I'm not the kind of person
who films people on the sly.

164
00:10:33,008 --> 00:10:34,676
I'll let you slide
if you apologize and delete it,

165
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:35,719
so think wisely.

166
00:10:37,471 --> 00:10:38,805
But I wasn't filming you.

167
00:10:45,228 --> 00:10:47,230
-What's going on?
-She was filming us.

168
00:10:47,898 --> 00:10:50,025
Probably going to upload it
for the comments.

169
00:10:53,695 --> 00:10:55,072
ZERO COMMENTS

170
00:10:58,784 --> 00:11:00,535
For the comments?

171
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:03,580
Yeah, comments!

172
00:11:03,663 --> 00:11:04,664
I'd love some comments.

173
00:11:04,748 --> 00:11:06,541
The more, the better.

174
00:11:06,625 --> 00:11:10,670
I didn't get a single snarky comment
despite the soapy ending.

175
00:11:10,754 --> 00:11:14,132
Do you know how humiliating it is
to have zero comments for 100 episodes?

176
00:11:16,510 --> 00:11:17,844
Don't change the subject.

177
00:11:19,096 --> 00:11:20,097
Give it a rest.

178
00:11:20,806 --> 00:11:21,640
You weren't filming?

179
00:11:22,224 --> 00:11:23,058
No.

180
00:11:24,101 --> 00:11:25,018
She said she wasn't.

181
00:11:25,102 --> 00:11:27,646
I saw her. Hiding like this.

182
00:11:28,855 --> 00:11:29,689
I want to check.

183
00:11:29,773 --> 00:11:31,566
What are you doing?

184
00:11:31,650 --> 00:11:33,777
-Let go.
-Don't do it.

185
00:11:33,860 --> 00:11:34,861
I didn't film you.

186
00:11:44,079 --> 00:11:45,747
No, no.

187
00:11:45,831 --> 00:11:48,458
No, please, no.

188
00:11:54,506 --> 00:11:57,134
The screen's cracked.
What are you going to do about this?

189
00:11:57,217 --> 00:11:59,052
How could you do this!

190
00:11:59,136 --> 00:12:00,178
I can't believe this!

191
00:12:00,262 --> 00:12:01,763
You should have just shown me.

192
00:12:03,223 --> 00:12:04,057
I'm sorry, kid.

193
00:12:04,141 --> 00:12:06,768
He's very sensitive about being filmed.

194
00:12:06,852 --> 00:12:08,728
That's why he overreacted.

195
00:12:08,812 --> 00:12:10,605
We'll compensate you for the damage.

196
00:12:13,275 --> 00:12:14,192
Forget it!

197
00:12:18,864 --> 00:12:20,699
Do you know why students wear uniforms?

198
00:12:25,162 --> 00:12:26,621
So they can be identified.

199
00:12:27,414 --> 00:12:31,501
If any footage of this turns up online,
I'll make you regret it.

200
00:12:34,713 --> 00:12:36,089
Asshole!

201
00:12:38,008 --> 00:12:38,842
Hey!

202
00:12:39,509 --> 00:12:40,635
Are you still here?

203
00:12:41,344 --> 00:12:43,221
Just get in and come with us
or we'll be late.

204
00:12:43,305 --> 00:12:44,514
Give me a second.

205
00:12:58,361 --> 00:12:59,696
Slow down.

206
00:13:24,804 --> 00:13:27,140
JEONJU MURIM GIRLS' HIGH

207
00:13:27,224 --> 00:13:33,188
CHAPTER 3:
SO, THAT ASSHOLE IS MY…

208
00:13:37,901 --> 00:13:39,903
Hey, Eui-ju!

209
00:13:42,030 --> 00:13:43,865
My best friend, Choi Go-ya.

210
00:13:43,949 --> 00:13:45,492
A gifted artist.

211
00:13:45,575 --> 00:13:49,120
She's been dating continuously
since sixth grade.

212
00:13:50,705 --> 00:13:54,125
I think I've put on two kilos.
All I did was eat and sleep.

213
00:13:56,836 --> 00:13:58,213
Yikes! What happened?

214
00:13:59,381 --> 00:14:01,049
Some guy moved in next door.

215
00:14:01,132 --> 00:14:03,718
He thought I was filming him
and asked to see my phone.

216
00:14:03,802 --> 00:14:05,428
I tried to stop him and…

217
00:14:06,846 --> 00:14:08,265
And you just let him be?

218
00:14:08,348 --> 00:14:12,060
You should have made him pay to repair it.
Or at least got his number to hound him.

219
00:14:12,143 --> 00:14:13,853
I didn't want any more to do with him.

220
00:14:13,937 --> 00:14:15,272
He looked like a complete jerk.

221
00:14:19,776 --> 00:14:21,111
What? Who is it?

222
00:14:21,903 --> 00:14:22,737
My ex.

223
00:14:23,363 --> 00:14:24,906
You broke up again?

224
00:14:24,990 --> 00:14:27,158
You said he was the hottest guy
at your art academy.

225
00:14:30,620 --> 00:14:33,039
When am I finally going to meet
my last love?

226
00:14:34,207 --> 00:14:35,750
Must be nice.

227
00:14:35,834 --> 00:14:37,586
I haven't even met my first love.

228
00:14:39,588 --> 00:14:41,131
Is the reason my novels are lame

229
00:14:41,756 --> 00:14:43,383
because I've never dated?

230
00:14:44,801 --> 00:14:45,802
Well…

231
00:14:46,553 --> 00:14:48,471
Dating might be helpful.

232
00:14:49,306 --> 00:14:51,766
But the more you do it,
the more it bursts your bubble.

233
00:14:53,059 --> 00:14:55,854
Since you still have
a rose-tinted view of dating,

234
00:14:55,937 --> 00:14:57,731
wouldn't that make you write better?

235
00:14:58,356 --> 00:15:00,442
-You think?
-Yeah.

236
00:15:00,525 --> 00:15:02,235
Why? Is it not going well?

237
00:15:02,319 --> 00:15:03,278
You said you were done.

238
00:15:04,029 --> 00:15:06,031
Yeah, I kind of am.

239
00:15:08,366 --> 00:15:10,535
When can I read it?

240
00:15:10,619 --> 00:15:12,495
You won't tell me the title
or your pen name.

241
00:15:13,371 --> 00:15:14,956
Are you sure we're friends?

242
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:17,459
I told you I'm going to take it
to my grave.

243
00:15:19,628 --> 00:15:20,962
What if you hit the big time?

244
00:15:21,046 --> 00:15:22,922
Are you still going to keep it secret?

245
00:15:23,548 --> 00:15:24,424
The big time?

246
00:15:25,634 --> 00:15:29,304
You'll be the first one I tell.

247
00:15:29,387 --> 00:15:32,015
I would love it if that happened.

248
00:15:36,561 --> 00:15:37,812
Hey, Go-ya! Eui-ju!

249
00:15:37,896 --> 00:15:39,856
-Hey!
-What's going on?

250
00:15:39,939 --> 00:15:42,359
-What is it?
-Quickly!

251
00:15:42,859 --> 00:15:43,693
Quickly!

252
00:15:43,777 --> 00:15:45,695
Hey! Can you see?

253
00:15:45,779 --> 00:15:48,406
I heard it was happening and it did!

254
00:15:48,490 --> 00:15:50,742
Wow. All the new teachers are guys.

255
00:15:50,825 --> 00:15:52,952
And not just any old guys.

256
00:15:53,036 --> 00:15:55,038
They're complete hotties. Total studs.

257
00:15:55,121 --> 00:15:56,915
I can't believe it.

258
00:15:56,998 --> 00:15:57,957
Take a look.

259
00:15:58,041 --> 00:16:00,377
Those looks! Those bodies!

260
00:16:00,460 --> 00:16:02,212
I'm going crazy.

261
00:16:02,295 --> 00:16:05,590
I've never wanted to go into
the teachers' office so much.

262
00:16:05,674 --> 00:16:07,300
This is unbearable!

263
00:16:07,884 --> 00:16:10,303
But Young-hee's locked the door
so we can't get in.

264
00:16:10,929 --> 00:16:14,808
She's introducing the new teachers,
so why is she keeping them from us?

265
00:16:16,518 --> 00:16:17,852
PE, Jung Gi-jeon.

266
00:16:17,936 --> 00:16:18,978
JUNG GI-JEON

267
00:16:19,062 --> 00:16:20,355
He represented Korea.

268
00:16:20,438 --> 00:16:23,775
He was the first Korean to finish
fourth in the luge at the Winter Games.

269
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:26,403
Damn it! Look at that body.

270
00:16:28,613 --> 00:16:31,116
Noh Da-ju. A polyglot.

271
00:16:31,199 --> 00:16:33,076
He'll teach Japanese and freshman English.

272
00:16:35,453 --> 00:16:38,665
He even did a TUD talk
on the secret to mastering languages.

273
00:16:39,833 --> 00:16:41,960
Rumor has it, he's the youngest son
of a chaebol family.

274
00:16:43,712 --> 00:16:45,463
I'm so glad I lived to see this.

275
00:16:51,177 --> 00:16:52,637
Korean literature, Yoon Dong-ju.

276
00:16:52,721 --> 00:16:56,558
Had a poem published
in Literary Youth in 2020.

277
00:16:56,641 --> 00:16:57,809
Something like My Mother.

278
00:17:00,019 --> 00:17:00,979
Found him.

279
00:17:02,897 --> 00:17:04,357
My last love.

280
00:17:06,651 --> 00:17:08,653
Hang on.

281
00:17:09,946 --> 00:17:11,531
That guy teaches Korean literature?

282
00:17:12,323 --> 00:17:13,366
Then surely not.

283
00:17:14,576 --> 00:17:15,410
No way.

284
00:17:16,035 --> 00:17:17,412
Ga Woo-su.

285
00:17:17,495 --> 00:17:18,997
Our new math teacher.

286
00:17:21,666 --> 00:17:26,671
Thanks to his outstanding research
in college…

287
00:17:26,755 --> 00:17:27,589
GA WOO-SU

288
00:17:27,672 --> 00:17:30,467
…several Ivy League schools
tried to recruit him,

289
00:17:31,176 --> 00:17:32,969
but he chose to come here instead.

290
00:17:36,473 --> 00:17:38,099
That asshole?

291
00:17:39,350 --> 00:17:41,060
He's a member of Mensa.

292
00:17:41,144 --> 00:17:42,187
Did you hear that?

293
00:17:43,229 --> 00:17:44,898
That's the kind of person he is.

294
00:17:44,981 --> 00:17:48,401
To put it another way, he's a math genius.

295
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:41,746
Dropped my…

296
00:18:46,835 --> 00:18:48,503
Did you see?

297
00:18:48,586 --> 00:18:50,713
Da-ju is just my type.

298
00:18:50,797 --> 00:18:52,882
The age of Ha E-den is finally over.

299
00:18:52,966 --> 00:18:54,509
Hey, how can you even compare?

300
00:18:54,592 --> 00:18:57,262
Ha E-den was just a little cute.

301
00:18:58,680 --> 00:19:01,599
Are you talking about me?
This early in the morning?

302
00:19:02,892 --> 00:19:04,519
HA E-DEN
MUSIC TEACHER

303
00:19:06,437 --> 00:19:07,689
Not at all.

304
00:19:08,690 --> 00:19:11,025
Oh, Go-ya. That was cold. That hurt.

305
00:19:11,734 --> 00:19:14,362
Thank you for being
our temporary homeroom teacher.

306
00:19:14,904 --> 00:19:16,698
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

307
00:19:23,204 --> 00:19:24,539
-Hello, sir.
-Good morning.

308
00:19:24,622 --> 00:19:25,582
No, it's not good.

309
00:19:26,291 --> 00:19:28,543
Have they lost their minds all together?

310
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:37,927
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH 11TH GRADE CLASS 2

311
00:19:39,846 --> 00:19:42,515
From now on, I'm going to put on
full make-up every day.

312
00:19:42,599 --> 00:19:44,309
Who have you got your eye on?

313
00:19:45,059 --> 00:19:46,936
His name is Dong-ju.

314
00:19:47,020 --> 00:19:48,229
My future husband.

315
00:19:49,314 --> 00:19:51,649
What should I major in
to be the perfect wife and mother?

316
00:19:51,733 --> 00:19:54,068
I think he'd like the quiet, modest type.

317
00:19:56,696 --> 00:19:58,781
I like the Japanese teacher.

318
00:19:58,865 --> 00:20:00,033
Get back to your lashes.

319
00:20:03,453 --> 00:20:04,996
-Who are you going for?
-For what?

320
00:20:05,079 --> 00:20:06,873
Your bias?

321
00:20:06,956 --> 00:20:07,957
We shouldn't overlap.

322
00:20:08,041 --> 00:20:10,460
Forget it. Bias? What a crock.

323
00:20:11,044 --> 00:20:13,379
But he's not even your type.

324
00:20:13,463 --> 00:20:14,672
My type's changed.

325
00:20:15,965 --> 00:20:17,342
Hang on a sec.

326
00:20:18,426 --> 00:20:20,845
-I just got a chill.
-Why?

327
00:20:20,929 --> 00:20:22,972
That means one of those four

328
00:20:23,598 --> 00:20:26,768
is going to be our new homeroom teacher.

329
00:20:29,896 --> 00:20:31,064
Shut up!

330
00:20:35,068 --> 00:20:38,029
EUN HA-SU
TOP OF THE SCHOOL, PRESENCE

331
00:20:38,571 --> 00:20:39,489
Will you be quiet?

332
00:20:42,116 --> 00:20:43,743
Class hasn't started yet.

333
00:20:43,826 --> 00:20:46,371
At least don't disturb others.

334
00:20:49,916 --> 00:20:51,292
She thinks she owns the place.

335
00:20:52,669 --> 00:20:54,003
Fancy a snack?

336
00:20:54,754 --> 00:20:55,922
Shall we pop out?

337
00:20:59,592 --> 00:21:00,593
Where are you going?

338
00:21:06,724 --> 00:21:08,643
BRACKET BY SPORT

339
00:21:08,726 --> 00:21:10,853
KOREAN LITERATURE TIMETABLE

340
00:21:10,937 --> 00:21:12,105
MR. GA WOO-SU

341
00:21:12,188 --> 00:21:15,441
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH
11TH GRADE TEACHERS' OFFICE

342
00:21:36,963 --> 00:21:39,298
KOREAN LITERATURE TIMETABLE

343
00:21:41,926 --> 00:21:43,428
Are you doing coloring?

344
00:21:45,054 --> 00:21:47,098
It's so I don't get confused.

345
00:21:52,478 --> 00:21:53,312
Are you feeling off?

346
00:21:53,980 --> 00:21:54,939
Want some antacids?

347
00:21:55,523 --> 00:21:58,026
No, I'll be fine.

348
00:22:17,211 --> 00:22:18,421
Are you disinfecting?

349
00:22:19,088 --> 00:22:20,298
Don't be so weird.

350
00:22:20,381 --> 00:22:21,340
Butt out.

351
00:22:23,551 --> 00:22:25,178
In the jungle of the workplace,

352
00:22:25,261 --> 00:22:27,597
don't you know standing out
means certain death?

353
00:22:28,264 --> 00:22:30,183
You know nothing
about the ways of the world.

354
00:22:30,808 --> 00:22:32,310
Switch with me. I can't take him.

355
00:22:32,393 --> 00:22:33,644
Don't be like that.

356
00:22:34,479 --> 00:22:36,856
I want to sit facing you.

357
00:22:36,939 --> 00:22:38,649
I miss you even when I can see you.

358
00:22:39,525 --> 00:22:41,819
Just stay there. It's designated seating.

359
00:22:41,903 --> 00:22:43,529
I don't want to sit facing that bat.

360
00:22:43,613 --> 00:22:44,739
What!

361
00:22:51,788 --> 00:22:53,414
I told you not to call me that.

362
00:22:54,540 --> 00:22:58,920
That word is like Voldemort to me.
I don't even want it on my lips.

363
00:22:59,003 --> 00:23:00,171
Don't you know I hate it?

364
00:23:00,963 --> 00:23:03,257
Of course you do. That's why you said it.

365
00:23:03,341 --> 00:23:06,177
You're Ga Woo-su, the genius.
There's no way you don't know.

366
00:23:09,639 --> 00:23:11,516
My hippocampus actually does something.

367
00:23:11,599 --> 00:23:14,811
It doesn't just handle learning
and memory, it also regulates emotions.

368
00:23:15,686 --> 00:23:17,396
That's why I can't sit facing you.

369
00:23:22,276 --> 00:23:24,112
Don't insult my hippocampus.

370
00:23:24,195 --> 00:23:25,613
You memory freak!

371
00:23:25,696 --> 00:23:26,864
Hey, fruit bat!

372
00:23:26,948 --> 00:23:28,074
What? Glasses monkey!

373
00:23:28,157 --> 00:23:29,117
Glasses monkey?

374
00:23:30,159 --> 00:23:31,494
Will you two cut it out?

375
00:23:38,209 --> 00:23:40,044
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

376
00:23:40,128 --> 00:23:42,004
How do you know he's your last love?

377
00:23:42,088 --> 00:23:43,548
You only just met him.

378
00:23:45,883 --> 00:23:46,884
Love is…

379
00:23:47,969 --> 00:23:49,220
like the first snow.

380
00:23:49,303 --> 00:23:50,388
Love at first sight.

381
00:23:50,471 --> 00:23:51,597
When you see them,

382
00:23:53,015 --> 00:23:54,517
you know that person is meant for you.

383
00:23:55,601 --> 00:23:57,145
That's how it is, kiddo.

384
00:23:57,937 --> 00:24:00,231
It hits you when you least expect it.

385
00:24:02,817 --> 00:24:06,404
Then all those other guys you dated…

386
00:24:06,487 --> 00:24:08,239
None of them were your first snow?

387
00:24:09,323 --> 00:24:11,534
I thought they were,
but they were just frost.

388
00:24:13,911 --> 00:24:16,455
My first snow came today.

389
00:24:18,833 --> 00:24:21,127
When will I get my first snow?

390
00:24:22,587 --> 00:24:23,462
I told you.

391
00:24:24,213 --> 00:24:26,424
When you least expect it.

392
00:24:27,758 --> 00:24:28,718
Suddenly,

393
00:24:29,677 --> 00:24:31,012
when you're defenseless,

394
00:24:31,846 --> 00:24:33,890
-like a smack to the back of the head.
-Thank you.

395
00:24:33,973 --> 00:24:35,266
-Ouch!
-Bye.

396
00:24:37,560 --> 00:24:38,811
-How much?
-It's 2,000 won.

397
00:24:40,313 --> 00:24:41,981
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

398
00:24:42,773 --> 00:24:43,941
Lucky you.

399
00:24:44,025 --> 00:24:46,402
You're experiencing first snow
with the new teacher.

400
00:24:46,485 --> 00:24:48,404
Whereas my first meeting was a disaster.

401
00:24:49,405 --> 00:24:50,698
Whatever.

402
00:24:52,241 --> 00:24:53,826
Anyhow,

403
00:24:53,910 --> 00:24:55,453
that's why he mentioned uniforms.

404
00:24:55,536 --> 00:24:57,872
He was basically saying,
"I'll see you at school."

405
00:24:59,248 --> 00:25:02,668
What's the use in being a genius
if he has a shitty personality?

406
00:25:12,553 --> 00:25:13,554
What is it?

407
00:25:47,672 --> 00:25:49,215
NO WAY

408
00:25:49,298 --> 00:25:51,801
I'M YOUR HOMEROOM TEACHER

409
00:27:06,625 --> 00:27:08,627
Subtitle: Paul Carver

